<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Korea (
                        Muccio
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v07p2</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d365</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">365</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-08-07T21:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-08-07T21:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-07T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-07T21:00:00-05:00" n="365" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/8–849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-08T12:00:00+10:00">August 8, 1949—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>990. According information just received from Chinhae, Generalissimo took off
                    this morning about 10:30 presumably to return Formosa. Text joint <hi rend="italic">communiqué</hi> issued on termination conversations being
                    telegraphed separately.<note n="1" xml:id="d365fn1">See <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>President and Mrs. Rhee expected return Seoul Tuesday morning.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss>.<note n="2" xml:id="d365fn2">Commander in Chief, U.S. Army Forces in the Far East
                        (MacArthur).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
